cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "Structured Emergence: Behavioral Signatures of Ambiguity Processing in Transformer-Based Language Models"
abstract: >-
  Pre-registered cross-architecture behavioral study of ambiguity processing in large
  language models. Demonstrates that ambiguous input produces a large, replicable
  increase in output token count across four model families (Gemma, Qwen, Llama,
  EXAONE), while the linguistic expression of uncertainty (hedging) is
  training-dependent. Introduces the term "fossil emotion" for training-dependent
  epistemic postures that can be transferred between models through distillation.
